---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CopyPrompt from "../components/CopyPrompt.astro";

const setupPrompt = `Set up this repo to use srid/agency by following the instructions at
https://github.com/srid/agency/blob/master/docs/agency-setup.md`;

const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<BaseLayout title="agency">
  <header class="topbar">
    <span class="topbar-mark">srid<span class="slash">/</span>agency</span>
    <a href="https://github.com/srid/agency" rel="noopener">github ↗</a>
  </header>

  <section class="hero wrap">
    <h1 class="hero-mark">agency<span class="dot">.</span></h1>
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">a workflow for coding agents</p>

    <p class="hero-slogan">
      a loop you can<br />
      <span class="accent-magenta">leave alone.</span>
    </p>

    <p class="hero-tag">
      Two skills. <em>talk</em> for design. <em>do</em> for shipping.
      End-to-end, every diff.
    </p>

    <CopyPrompt text={setupPrompt} />
  </section>

  <section class="sec wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">01</span>
      <div>
        <p class="sec-label">the loop</p>
        <h2 class="h2">two entry points, <span class="accent-magenta">never one.</span></h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pair">
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-cyan">/talk &nbsp;·&nbsp; spec isn't obvious</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">Sketch first. Ship later.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          Discuss, read, sketch. Run <code>hickey</code> + <code>lowy</code> on
          the sketch. Read-only. Hand the converged plan to <code>do</code>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-magenta">/do &nbsp;·&nbsp; "done" is concrete</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">Research → review → ship.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          Implement, structural review, quality gate, CI, merge. Each fix lands
          as its own commit.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body" style="margin-top: 2.25rem;">
      <p>
        <strong><code>/do</code> has no design phase.</strong> Pasting a thin
        plan into <code>/do</code> produces a thin implementation. The fix is
        to do the design work in <code class="cmd-cyan">/talk</code> first.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">02</span>
      <div>
        <p class="sec-label">feedback</p>
        <h2 class="h2">the loop is only as <span class="accent-cyan">good as its signal.</span></h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <p>
        E2e tests are a prerequisite, not a nice-to-have. Unit tests and
        type-checks alone don't tell the agent whether its change actually
        worked.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ul class="triple" style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
      <li class="triple-cell is-magenta">
        <p class="triple-label">frontend</p>
        <p class="triple-body">
          Screenshot evidence on every PR.
          <a href="https://github.com/srid/agency/issues/106" rel="noopener">#106</a>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="triple-cell is-cyan">
        <p class="triple-label">nix infra</p>
        <p class="triple-body">
          NixOS VM tests. Closest thing to an executable spec the agent can
          drive.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="triple-cell is-lime">
        <p class="triple-label">backend / library</p>
        <p class="triple-body">
          Fast, deterministic e2e. 30s deterministic beats 10min thorough.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="sec wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">03</span>
      <div>
        <p class="sec-label">state</p>
        <h2 class="h2">one PR <span class="accent-lime">at a time.</span></h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pair">
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-lime">within a PR</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">.do-results.json + stop-guard.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          Per-step lifecycle and timing. The Stop hook blocks bail-outs while a
          run is <code>working</code>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-magenta">across PRs</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">No memory. By design.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          Land each PR end-to-end in a day or two. For larger work, <code class="cmd-cyan">/talk</code>
          produces a phased issue, <code>/do</code> consumes each phase.
          <a href="https://github.com/juspay/kolu/issues/514" rel="noopener">kolu#514</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">04</span>
      <div>
        <p class="sec-label">structure</p>
        <h2 class="h2">what tests <span class="accent-magenta">don't catch.</span></h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <p>
        Two structural-review passes run post-implement, in parallel. Each
        finding lands as its own commit; the full ledger ships as a PR
        comment.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pair">
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-magenta">hickey</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">Accidental complexity.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          After Rich Hickey's <em>Simple Made Easy</em>. Catches the
          complecting tests pass straight through.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-cyan">lowy</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">Volatility-based decomposition.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          After Juval Lowy's <em>Righting Software</em>. Module boundaries
          should encapsulate axes of change.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body" style="margin-top: 2.25rem;">
      <p>
        Full framing:
        <a href="https://kolu.dev/blog/hickey-lowy/" rel="noopener">Hickey/Lowy on kolu.dev</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="foot wrap">
    <p class="colophon">
      <a href="https://github.com/srid/agency" rel="noopener"
        >github.com/srid/agency</a
      >
      <span>·</span>
      <a href="https://kolu.dev" rel="noopener">sister · kolu.dev</a>
      <span>·</span>
      <span>mit · {year}</span>
    </p>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
